The Chronicle Mashudu Netsianda, Senior Reporter
ZANU-PF candidate Cde Kidwell Mujuru romped to victory in Saturday’s Bulawayo Ward 28 (Cowdray Park) by elections after garnering 1 899 vote, beating his closest contender Ms Nomagugu Mloyi of MDC-Alliance, by 670 votes. Ms Mloyi got 1229 votes while her colleague Mr Collet Ndlovu also from the same opposition party garnered 221 votes. The Nelson Chamisa led opposition party fielded two candidates. Zanu-PF got more votes than the two MDC Alliance candidates combined. The elections had 18 candidates vying for the ward seat, which fell vacant following the death of MDC Alliance councillor Hapson Nyasha Ncube.